EPAM Systems are looking to recruit a Delivery Manager – (Financial Services, Infrastructure, CI/CD, Cloud) for a high-profile Financial Services client in London
JOB OVERVIEW
We’re looking for a Delivery Manager who can help us: – manage and drive key initiatives and projects – work closely with talent acquisition teams to identify the best fit staff for your teams – work closely with development teams to implement and deliver business functionality across a range of different platforms and systems – handle stakeholder relationships – manage projects budgets, schedule, scope, priorities, team allocation, and oversee the implementation all the way until delivery – coordinate releases to production – provide technical leadership – look after delivery teams based in Krakow, Wroclaw, Budapest, Weehawken, and London.
RESPONSIBILITIES You’ll be working in a global team that develops and maintains applications across Fixed Income (Rates & Credit), FX, Equities, and Group Operations IT. As Delivery Manager, you will work closely with colleagues in London and other locations as well as your business stakeholders to understand the business requirements and the overall programme context in IB Technology to ensure that deliveries align to multiple business/technology objectives and timescales REQUIREMENTS Infrastructure Background is highly desirable (servers, networking, etc) Experience with Tooling management Experience with CI/CD pipelines Cloud experience is great plus, but not mandatory with strong infra background Experience of integration with Development teams (e.g. pure Sysadmin is not ideal) Experience with stakeholder’s management and indirect influence on peers Good verbal and presentation skills – ability to work with large audience Experience of team management (ideally remote team) Ability to multi-task and run multiple projects in parallel Architectural skills are a plus
ABOUT EPAM
Ranked as #12 on Forbes’ List of 25 Fastest Growing Public Tech Companies for 2017, EPAM is committed to providing our global team of 30,100+ EPAMers with inspiring careers from day one. EPAMers lead with passion and honesty, and think creatively. Our people are the source of our success and we value collaboration, try to always understand our customers’ business, and strive for the highest standards of excellence. No matter where you are located, you’ll join a dedicated, diverse community that will help you discover your fullest potential.
